04-25T01:02:19Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```rust\r\ntrait Trait {\r\n    fn fun();\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn takes_static_fn(_: impl Fn() + 'static) {}\r\n\r\nfn test<T: Trait>() {\r\n    // these work\r\n    takes_static_fn(|| T::fun());\r\n    takes_static_fn(T::fun as fn());\r\n\r\n    // this seems like it ought to work\r\n    takes_static_fn(T::fun);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```console\r\nerror[E0310]: the parameter type `T` may not live long enough\r\n  --> src/lib.rs:12:5\r\n   |\r\n7  | fn test<T: Trait>() {\r\n   |         -- help: consider adding an explicit lifetime bound...: `T: 'static +`\r\n...\r\n12 |     takes_static_fn(T::fun);\r\n   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ ...so that the type `fn() {<T as Trait>::fun}` will meet its required lifetime bounds\r\n\r\nFor more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0310`.\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/89667/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/89667/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}